Reasoning: The paper discusses the interpretation of deep neural network models in computer vision tasks, specifically image classification and object detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel method for interpreting neural network models with attention mechanisms, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the relation between classification accuracy and attention-based heatmap, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper proposes an improved attention-based method, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
